# Sajtmaskin Terminology

## Site layers (top to bottom)

| Layer | What it is | URL pattern |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **Vercel** | Hosting platform. Deploys, domains, env vars, CDN. | vercel.com |
| **Sajtmaskin** | Our app. Own code-generation engine (default), manages projects, users, deploy flow. | sajtmaskin.se |
| **v0** (soft-deprecated) | AI code generation platform used as opt-in fallback only when `V0_FALLBACK_BUILDER=y`. | v0.dev, *.vusercontent.net |
| **Demo sites** | User-generated sites. Built by own engine, previewed in-app, deployed to Vercel. | *.vercel.app or custom domain |

## Pages in our app

### Start page (`/`)

The landing page with 4 entry modes shown as tabs/cards:

| Mode | Code name | Component | What it does |
|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| **Analyserad** (Wizard) | `wizard` | `PromptWizardModalV2` | 5-step guided questionnaire that builds a detailed prompt |
| **Kategori** (Templates) | `category` | `TemplateGallery` | Browse template categories, pick a starting point |
| **Audit** | `audit` | `SiteAuditSection` + `AuditModal` | Analyze an existing website URL, show improvement suggestions |
| **Fritext** (Freeform) | `freeform` | `PromptInput` | Type a free-text description directly |

All 4 modes lead to the **builder** via `/builder?buildMethod=<mode>&...`

Important language rule:
- Use **`Fritext`** in Swedish product/UI copy.
- Use **`freeform`** as the canonical code/query/API value.

### Builder (`/builder`)

The main workspace where the user iterates on their site:
- Left panel: chat interface (prompt, AI responses, version history)
- Right panel: live preview (iframe or app preview route)
- Header: model selection, scaffold mode, custom instructions, deploy button

### Admin (`/admin`)

Internal dashboard with tabs: Database, Environment, Analytics, Prompts.

## Key concepts

### Two operational lanes

When discussing generation architecture, prefer this mental model:

| Lane | What belongs here | What it is not |
|------|-------------------|----------------|
| **Runtime lane** | `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`, scaffold matching, scaffold serialization, preview/deploy generation flow | Not the template gallery, not raw external datasets |
| **Research lane** | `research/external-templates/reference-library/`, raw discovery under `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`, curated generated JSON in `src/lib/gen/template-library/` | Not the runtime scaffold registry |

Important rule:
- Treat the **template gallery** in `src/lib/templates/` as a product/UI discovery surface, not as a third generation lane.
- Do NOT describe the system as if runtime generation alternates between "templates" and "scaffolds". Runtime generation should be described as scaffold-driven.

### Builder model lanes (user-facing)

When discussing model selection inside the builder, use this lane vocabulary:

| Lane | Swedish label | What it controls | Where user picks it |
|------|---------------|------------------|---------------------|
| **Model lane** | `bygg-lane` | Main generation model for the actual build/refine stream | `Byggmodell` (`modelId` / `modelTier`) |
| **Product lane** | `prompt-lane` | Prompt-assist model used before build (rewrite/brief/spec support) | `Forbattra` + `Deep Brief Mode` |
| **Polish lane** | `billig/snabb/latt lane` | Low-cost text-only rewrite of the prompt input | `Skriv om` (`SAJTMASKIN_POLISH_MODEL`) |
| **Thinking flag** | `tankeflagga` | Extra reasoning behavior in generation metadata | `Thinking` toggle |

Important rules:
- Do NOT mix up `operational lanes` (runtime vs research) with `builder model lanes`.
- `Anthropic` can be selected in the **model lane** (build profile `anthropic`) and also in the **product lane** (`anthropic/*` assist model strings).
- The `Anthropic-jamforelse` preset intentionally aligns both model lane and product lane to Anthropic for apples-to-apples comparison.
- `Thinking` is not a lane and does not replace model or product lane selection.

### Template vs scaffold vs Vercel template

Three concepts that must not be mixed:

| Term | Swedish label | Meaning | Scope |
|------|---------------|---------|-------|
| **Sajtmaskin template gallery item** | `hemsidemall` or `kategori-mall` | A user-facing gallery entry from `src/lib/templates/`. For browsing and inspiration. NOT used at generation runtime. | Product/UI concept |
| **Runtime scaffold** | `grundmall` | One of ~10 internal starter projects in `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`. The engine uses these as a base instead of generating from scratch. Auto-selected by embedding matching or manually chosen. | Runtime generation concept |
| **Vercel Template** | `extern Vercel-template` | A public starter repo from vercel.com/templates. External reference only. | External ecosystem concept |

Research and curation concepts (not used at runtime):

| Term | Swedish label | Meaning |
|------|---------------|---------|
| **Reference dossier** | `referensdossier` | Curated per-template research package under `research/external-templates/reference-library/dossiers/`. Contains manifest, summary, selected files. Feeds into scaffold improvements via build scripts. |
| **Generated research artifact** | `genererad research-artefakt` | Committed JSON/embeddings in `src/lib/gen/template-library/` and `scaffold-research.generated.json`. Derived from dossiers at build time, consumed at runtime for template reference ranking. |
| **Raw discovery** | `rå upptäckt` | Noisy scrape output under `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`. Gitignored. Not runtime data. |

Architecture concepts:

| Term | Swedish label | Meaning |
|------|---------------|---------|
| **Multi-tenant** | `delad plattform` | One codebase serving many tenants. Describes the sajtmaskin app itself. |
| **Multi-project** | `separata kundprojekt` | One Vercel project per customer site. Describes deploy targets. |

Preferred terminology:
- Product UI copy: **`hemsidemall`** or **`kategori-mall`**
- `src/lib/templates/`: **`template gallery`** or **`gallery item`**
- `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`: **`scaffold`** or **`runtime scaffold`**
- Vercel's public library: **`Vercel template`** (always qualify)
- `research/external-templates/reference-library/dossiers/`: **`reference dossier`**
- `scaffold-research.generated.json` etc.: **`generated research artifact`**

Key rules:
- Do NOT call scaffolds just `templates` — that term is for the gallery.
- Do NOT describe dossiers as a second scaffold registry — they are research input.
- Do NOT imply dossiers are used at runtime — only their generated artifacts are.

### Common chat aliases

Treat common misspellings and spoken-style aliases as canonical platform names:

| Alias in chat | Canonical term |
|---------------|----------------|
| `Varicell`, `Vericell` | `Vercel` |
| `Veenol`, `Venol` | `v0` |

When answering, prefer canonical names (`Vercel`, `v0`) even if user writes an alias.

### Orchestrator terms

Use this vocabulary consistently for automation work:

- `orchestrator run` - the full dated execution folder under `.cursor/orchestrator/run/`
- `orchestrator agent` - the coordinator that plans, delegates, validates, and performs minor fixes
- `run roadmap` - the per-run `ROADMAP.md`
- `track plan` - an intermediate tier-2 plan for one broader workstream inside an orchestrator run
- `agent log` - a per-workload execution note written by the delegated agent
- `final sweep` - the closing cleanup and audit pass for dead code, ghost routes, stale files, and doc drift

Treat `/orchestrator` and `/automation` as the compact startup aliases for the
orchestrator-run system.

### Generation pipeline

The own engine generation flow:

1. **Prompt assist** (optional) — rewrites/briefs the user prompt before generation
2. **Prompt orchestration** — budget/strategy for the message (`direct`, `summarize`, `phase_plan_build_polish`)
3. **Scaffold resolution** — auto-match, manual pick, or off
4. **Context orchestration** (`orchestrate.ts`) — builds scaffold context, route plan, capability inference, contract inference
5. **System prompt** (`system-prompt.ts`) — STATIC_CORE (~6-8K tokens, cached) + dynamic context (custom instructions, build intent, scaffold, brief, theme, references, KB matches, template references)
6. **Generation stream** — own engine via OpenAI, or v0 fallback
7. **Post-generation** — autofix, esbuild validation, URL expansion, file parsing, scaffold merge

### Custom instructions

Two tiers in `src/lib/builder/defaults.ts`:

- **CORE_CUSTOM_INSTRUCTIONS** — always active: tech stack, shadcn setup, language, accessibility
- **EXTENDED_CUSTOM_INSTRUCTIONS** — only when scaffold is `off`: design system execution, component usage, Tailwind, visual identity, layout, motion, images, Figma workflow

Selection: `getDefaultCustomInstructions(scaffoldMode)`:
- scaffold `auto` or `manual` → CORE only (scaffold + STATIC_CORE covers design)
- scaffold `off` → CORE + EXTENDED (no scaffold, needs full design guidance)

The user can edit these in the builder header dialog. `isDefaultCustomInstructions()` detects manual edits.

### Research pipeline terms

Use this pipeline vocabulary consistently:

1. `raw discovery` -> scrape output such as `research/external-templates/raw-discovery/`
2. `raw template dataset` -> `_sidor`-style local datasets used for curation
3. `reference dossier` -> curated per-template package under `research/external-templates/reference-library/dossiers/`
4. `generated research artifacts` -> committed JSON/embeddings in `src/lib/gen/template-library/` and scaffold research JSON
5. `runtime scaffold` -> internal starter used directly by generation

### Build method (`BuildMethod`)

How the user entered the builder. One of:
`wizard` | `category` | `audit` | `freeform` | `kostnadsfri`

### Engine path naming

- Use `own-engine` as the canonical technical value in metadata, routes, and logs.
- Use `egen motor` only as the Swedish display label in UI copy.

### Build intent (`BuildIntent`)

What the user wants to build:
- `website` - standard multi-page website (default)
- `app` - interactive app with logic/flows
- `template` - compact 1-2 page template

### Internal theme vs Figma vs v0 design system

These concepts are also different and should NOT be mixed:

| Term | Variable/type name | Meaning | Scope |
|------|--------------------|---------|-------|
| **Internal theme preset** | `designTheme` / `themeColors` | Sajtmaskin's own theme preset and derived semantic colors used to steer the own engine's output. | Internal builder + own engine |
| **Figma reference** | attachment with `purpose: "figma-reference"` | A visual reference used to guide hierarchy, spacing, composition, and styling. Not a reusable component system by itself. | Prompt/reference concept |
| **v0 Design System** | `designSystemId` / `v0DesignSystemId` | External registry-backed design system consumed by v0. Tokens/components/registry concept, separate from our own theme presets. | External v0 integration |

Preferred terminology:
- Say **`designTheme`** or **`theme preset`** for Sajtmaskin's internal theme choice
- Say **`Figma reference`** for linked/imported Figma used as visual inspiration
- Say **`v0 design system`** or **`external design system`** for registry-backed `designSystemId`

Important rule:
- Do NOT call `designTheme` a `design system` without qualifier
- Do NOT describe a Figma file as if it were the same thing as a registry-backed `designSystemId`
- When needed in code discussions, prefer `v0DesignSystemId` as the clearer name for the external concept

### Project

A sajtmaskin project that groups chats, versions, and deployments together.
Stored in our database. Has an `appProjectId` (ours) and optionally a
`v0ProjectId` (legacy, from v0 fallback era).

### Chat

A conversation in the builder. Each chat produces versions. With own engine
the chat is stored locally; with v0 fallback it maps to a v0 chat ID.

### Version

A snapshot of generated code from one generation turn. Contains files
(the actual React/Next.js code) and optionally a preview URL.

### Preview

Own engine uses an app-internal preview route to render the generated code.
v0 fallback uses `demoUrl` (temporary URL on `*.vusercontent.net`).

The **Sandbox** (`@vercel/sandbox` via `SandboxModal`) is opt-in for testing
server-side behavior before deploying.

### Deployment

When the user clicks "Deploy":
1. Fetch the version's files
2. Process images (upload to Vercel Blob if needed)
3. Create a Vercel deployment via Vercel REST API
4. Return a permanent URL on the user's Vercel project

